// Python PEP8
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends using 4 spaces per indentation level and avoiding tabs."}
{"rule": "PEP8 suggests limiting all lines to a maximum of 79 characters."}
{"rule": "PEP8 advises breaking long lines using Pythonâ€™s implied line continuation inside parentheses, brackets, and braces."}
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends imports to be on separate lines and grouped in the order: standard library, third-party, local application."}
{"rule": "PEP8 discourages wildcard imports (from module import *)." }
{"rule": "PEP8 suggests placing imports at the top of the file."}
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends using blank lines to separate functions, classes, and blocks of code inside functions."}
{"rule": "PEP8 advises using spaces around operators and after commas, but not directly inside parentheses, brackets, or braces."}
{"rule": "PEP8 discourages extra whitespace before commas, semicolons, or colons."}
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends avoiding multiple statements on the same line."}
{"rule": "PEP8 suggests using a single space after the # symbol in inline comments."}
{"rule": "PEP8 advises that block comments should be indented to the same level as the code they describe."}
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends using docstrings to describe all public modules, functions, classes, and methods."}
{"rule": "PEP8 suggests naming classes using CapWords convention (CamelCase)." }
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends naming functions and variables in lowercase with words separated by underscores."}
{"rule": "PEP8 advises constants to be written in all uppercase letters with underscores separating words."}
{"rule": "PEP8 suggests using self for instance methods and cls for class methods as the first argument."}
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends avoiding ambiguous names like l, O, or I for variables."}
{"rule": "PEP8 advises breaking long expressions before binary operators, placing the operator at the beginning of the new line."}
{"rule": "PEP8 suggests using explicit is not None checks instead of equality comparisons to None."}
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends using isinstance() instead of type() for type comparisons."}
{"rule": "PEP8 advises exception names should end with Error."}
{"rule": "PEP8 recommends using try/except for exception handling, not catching overly broad exceptions."}
{"rule": "PEP8 suggests using with statements for resource management (e.g., file handling)."}
{"rule": "PEP8 advises keeping code visually consistent and readable, prioritizing clarity over cleverness."}
